   A minimal fix involves ensuring that the program does not use the `data`
   pointer after the memory has been freed. One efficient approach is setting
   the pointer to `NULL` after freeing the memory, and handling `NULL` pointers
   accordingly.
   ```c
   free(data);
   data = NULL; // Prevent use after free by nullifying the pointer
   
   if (data != NULL) {
       printLine(data);
   }
   ```
   
